rComments: The material itself is very simple & easy to understand. BUT get ready to read!! This guy copy pastes big sections of the textbook onto the exam & makes you guess if they're true or false. You have to make sure you read & remember exactly what you read which is sometimes difficult to do. He gives away participation marks though which is good.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: This class is very organized and easy! He gives you hints on what to study for the midterms and the final. Exam questions are all from the slides and the textbook. You get participation marks for attendance and in-class assignments (2-3 through out the semester).

It's an easy grade. All MC exams and participation marks for being in class and doing in-class assignments. Lectures are dry and he speaks slowly, but overall he's a good professor and it's well worth it. If you're in class he'll give you plenty of exam question subjects, so be there!

He's such a sweet person and a great professor! Assignments aren't difficult and midterms are easy as long as you read the textbook. Go to his lectures, he knows what he's talking about and is great at conveying material, and more often than not he'll give away A LOT of midtermexam answers during class!

ADORED & found him entertaining. He does speak slowly & repeats, so classes can lag but he's so passionate, loves answering questions, & is just so sweet & animated you can't help but like him. Read text for exams- essential. Go to exam review classes- recycles questions on final. SIGN ATTENDANCE SHEET- participation mark giveaway. LISTEN for hints

Lectures are extremely boring! Though he gives hints at what to study for the exam you will still have no idea what to actually study. Also, very unhelpful when it comes to discussing your mark. Girlfriend tried to talk to him about her mark and he would cut her off and not let her talk. Would not recommend his classes.
really good professor, the class was really clear and the exams are easy. help me a lot.

He is always well prepared for class and has a good insight in what he is talking about. Passionate about his work and seems to have a lot of experience. Couldn't ask for a better person to be teaching this subject.
He used to go into multi-national companies and train employees on diversity and cultural communication. This class feels like one of his corporate training seminars.

Very easy to follow, although sometimes it got quite boring since he tends to repeat stuff and give out too many examples. Super helpful and always makes a note of stuff that's important for the exam and quizzes

Un professeur extraordinaire ! Il est intéressant et en plus il a travaillé dans le monde du développement international, alors quoi de mieux que quelqu'un qui connais «Hands-On» le sujet. Je suggère grandement ce cours :)

This teacher loves what he does and I thought he was particularly passionate about the communications and media field. He tried to please the students way too much according to me, thus got mixed up with exam and quiz dates. I however thought he was a really good and helpful teacher. He knows his stuff.

Exam is easy as long as you study the powerpoints. Lets you know when certain info is important and will be on exam. He repeats certain things over and over, it gets kind of annoying, but at least you know it's important and that you should keep it in mind for the next test.
the notes are everywhere, incomprehensible. He always repeats the same material over and over again, it gets really boring at points. He's class is not interesting at all.
he has a nice guy face and he is nice, BUT HIS LECTURE IS PRETTY MUCH ABOUT HIM READING OFF THE POWERPOINT.....AND HIS AMAZING LIFE

Trying to study for his exam was like trying to study for a trivia game show. There was practically no way of knowing what was going to be on the exam. What should have been a straight foward test seemed totally random even though I went to every class and did all the readings.

Lectures were not all bad, textbook reading was mostly dry and the midterm that was suppposed to be an easy 50 multiple choice turned out to be a nightmare (even though i attended all classes and did all the readings....) how does that work? most of the class did poorly on the midterm FYI
He's okay..

This guy really knows his stuff -however he lacks the ability to capture the attention of his class and as a result tends to have low attendance ratings in most of his classes. He does provide very constructive criticism when you ask him for his opinion for writing essays, etc which is always a good thing! Overall, I would take him as a prof again.

Slowest talker ever. His voice is like a lullaby. Not a bad guy, and he knows what he's talking about... and his course is easy... but he's just SO boring! If you hate boring teachers this guy's not for you, but if you can handle that and what an easier course load then please, by all means, stick with him.
terrible soooooo boring

Very ok, he is not boring, its just that the class seems a waste of time, since what he goes about are stories in real life, that relate to the material somehow but are not gona be in the exam..so basically he dozes off the subject, i suggest attending class but reading abook or sumthng while he gets off track..i recomment this class:)

he is the nicest guy in the WORLD... but... he is sooooo monotone that you kind of doze off in class.. best advice read the book and go over his slides... i never really needed to be in class he didnt take attendance in mine.. but hes just sooo nice i feel bad... very intelligent as well... just boring
ok
No Comments

Nice person, but he is very monotone.  And just a word of advice: YOU SHOULD NOT TAKE ANY OF THIS PROFESSOR'S CLASSES IF YOU DON'T WANT TO BE GRADED ON YOUR NUMBER OF ABSENCES, MOST OF THE STUDENTS WERE ALDULTS AND HE STILL TOOK ATTENDANCE. HE SHOULD GET A LIFE AND REALIZE THAT BECAUSE A PERSON IS NOT IN CLASS, DOES NOT MEAN HE IS BAD STUDENT.

HE IS SOOO NICE! He is extremely fair in everything, from marking to personal viewpoints.  He may be a little dry but i've had way worse. I did a summer class, and we only had to do a group paper (easy) and a midterm and final (also easy). the text was a good read but useless in terms of the course.Can relate all he taught to real life
Oh boy. The sad thing is that he is such a nice person. He really is. But he is SOOOOO boring. As mentioned, his lectures have nothing to do with the exam so there is no incentive to pay attention.
Bahahahahahahaah

How this guy ever got hired is a mystery to me. His lectures are boring and he spends half the time talking about himself. Class time is wasted time, nothing useful because everything for the exam and midterm came from the textbook. Very poor rapport with the class.
He brags a little too much but he is still a very nice prof. Too bad he is so darn BORING. I blame his lectures for my caffeine addiction.

I don't call this teaching. You will learn nothing with him other than how excellent he is and the great exploits he has accomplished. He justifies no claims, classes are dreadfully long and boring. I have never said this before but this is a complete waste of money and time.

Prof. Champagne should be fired. Wastes  lectures with war stories from his days at TVO and CIDA. He speaks in a monotone voice, not interactive. Makes grand claims without acknowledging criticisms or contrasting viewpoints. Some of us have named this THE CHAMPAGNE BUBBLE!
horrible professor. Dry, monotone, uncreative and completely unavailable. Is never in his office hours. Sorry but he tarnishes the reputation of Ottawa U.
This prof needs some private industry experience. His approach is laggard and classes are dreadfully boring!
Needs to learn how to speak proper french. Don't even need to go to class, it's all on the net.
Sucked.
This guy doesnt get it.  Useless.  You can write anything and get away with it if you throw in a couple lenghty words.
